    <summary>Identifies the color primaries of a color space using CICP (Coding-Independent Code Points) codes from ITU-T H.273.</summary>
    <remarks><format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[
## Remarks

`SKColorspacePrimariesCicp` enumerates the color-primary standards defined in ITU-T H.273 (ISO/IEC 23091-2). These values are used with <xref:SkiaSharp.SKColorSpace.CreateCicp(SkiaSharp.SKColorspacePrimariesCicp,SkiaSharp.SKColorspaceTransferFnCicp)> to create a color space from standardized CICP codes, as found in HEIF, AVIF, and other modern image formats.

## Examples

```csharp
// Create an sRGB-equivalent color space using CICP codes
using var cs = SKColorSpace.CreateCicp(
    SKColorspacePrimariesCicp.Rec709,
    SKColorspaceTransferFnCicp.Iec6196621);
```
]]></format></remarks>
  </Docs>
